\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 4. Follower Milestones (per-hustle scaling)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Directly reskins AdCap's 25/50/100/200/300/400 unit thresholds:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 At 
\f0\b 25 / 50 / 100 / 200 / 300 / 400 units
\f1\b0  of a given Hustle owned, its cycle time is halved.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 At the same thresholds, that Hustle's income is doubled.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 These stack: owning 400 Day Trading Screenshots compresses a 1-second cycle down toward a fraction of a second, same math AdCap uses to shrink the Oil Company from 10 hours to 9 seconds.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 In-game framing: each threshold is a 
\f0\b Verification Tier
\f1\b0  \'97 "10K followers," "Blue Check," "Verified Guru," "Feature in Forbes (paid placement)." The UI shows a follower-count bar per Hustle instead of a raw unit count, but under the hood it's the same integer AdCap tracks.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 5. Viral Moment (the "Capitalist unlock")\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 When 
\f0\b every owned Hustle simultaneously reaches the same milestone tier
\f1\b0 , the whole account "goes viral" \'97 a universal 2x multiplier applies to all income at once, identical to AdCap's Capitalist unlocks. This is the strongest lever in the game and should be telegraphed clearly in the UI (a progress ring showing "3 of 5 hustles at Tier 3") so players actively level hustles evenly instead of dumping everything into one.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 6. Ghostwriters (the "managers")\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Three tiers, matching AdCap's Normal / Accountant / Discount manager structure:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Normal Ghostwriter
\f1\b0  \'97 bought with Cash. Automates a Hustle's posting cycle so it runs without taps, including while the app is closed. This is what turns the game idle.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Publicist
\f1\b0  (Accountant equivalent) \'97 bought by sacrificing Clout, not Cash. Switches the Hustle's display from "per post" to "per second" and cuts that Hustle's next-unit cost by 10%. Lost on Rebrand, must be rebought each run; the Clout spent on it is gone for good.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 PR Firm
\f1\b0  (Discount manager equivalent) \'97 cash-only, cuts unit cost by ~99.999% for its Hustle. Late-game only, first platform only (see Section 8).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 7. Rebrand (the "reset"/prestige action)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The player can wipe the current persona at any time: all Hustles and Cash reset to zero.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 In exchange, lifetime Cash earned converts into Clout using a square-root curve, mirroring AdCap's angel formula: 
\f4\fs26 Clout gained = sqrt(lifetimeCash / divisor) \uc0\u8722  Clout already held
\f1\fs24 .\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Clout is permanent and stacks additively at +2% income each, so 50 Clout = +100% income (2x), matching AdCap's angel math exactly.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Clout can also be 
\f0\b spent
\f1\b0  (sacrificed, permanently) on powerful one-time upgrades or Publicists \'97 but spending it removes its passive bonus, so the game should warn the player before any Clout spend that costs more than ~15% of their current total, same as AdCap's confirmation-prompt threshold.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Framing: Rebranding is literally "deleting the account and starting a new persona," which fits the LARP theme better than a generic "prestige" button \'97 the player's old following is gone, but their 
\f2\i reputation for knowing how to go viral
\f1\i0  (Clout) carries over.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

